        <description>&lt;hr /&gt;&#13;
&lt;h3&gt;"Default - All Computers" Action Group ID&lt;/h3&gt;&#13;
&lt;p&gt;Set this to the &lt;strong&gt;ID&lt;/strong&gt; of the &lt;strong&gt;Default - All Computers&lt;/strong&gt; Action Group (&lt;i&gt;not to be confused with Computer Groups&lt;/i&gt;).&lt;br /&gt;&#13;
To find this ID in Tanium, navigate to &lt;strong&gt;Administration&lt;/strong&gt; &gt; &lt;strong&gt;Actions&lt;/strong&gt; &gt; &lt;strong&gt;Action Groups&lt;/strong&gt;.  Click the three vertical lines at the top-right of the list and make sure that the &lt;strong&gt;ID&lt;/strong&gt; column is checked. Find the group called "Default - All Computers", and grab the value from the ID column and copy it into this property.&lt;br /&gt;&#13;
Note: If left blank, the default behavior in Tanium may be to use all computers.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;
&lt;strong&gt;Default&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;i&gt;(none; must be set)&lt;/i&gt;</description>
